Interface Extent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    InputExtent, OutputExtent
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Clipboard, ReorderingExtent, World
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDelegateExtent, AbstractLoggingExtent, AbstractWorld, BlockArrayClipboard, BlockBagExtent, BlockChangeLimiter, BlockQuirkExtent, BlockTransformExtent, ChangeSetExtent, ChunkLoadingExtent, DataValidatorExtent, EditSession, FastModeExtent, ForgetfulExtentBuffer, LastAccessExtentCache, LocalWorld, LocalWorldAdapter, MaskingExtent, MultiStageReorder, NullExtent, NullWorld, SurvivalModeExtent

    public interface Extent
extends InputExtent, OutputExtent
    A world, portion of a world, clipboard, or other object that can have blocks set or entities placed.

    the get____() portion, the set____() portion

      • getEntities

        java.util.List<? extends Entity> getEntities(Region region)
        Get a list of all entities within the given region.

        If the extent is not wholly loaded (i.e. a world being simulated in the game will not have every chunk loaded), then this list may not be incomplete.

        Parameters:
        region - the region in which entities must be contained
        Returns:
        a list of entities
